l; and his work as an international lecturer. In examining Oz’s life and work, Alter brings together testimony from Oz and his circle, as well as close readings of his central works, to present the inner world and public persona of Amos Oz.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, IsraelivBiography. 0aAuthors, IsraelixBiography. 0aAuthors, Palestinian ArabxBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300274387?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300274387423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300274387/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles